<subSubSection id="91E06561FFC20D25FCC3F883FBC9F7CD" pageId="5" pageNumber="460" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D94536EAFFC20D25FCC3F883FBC9F7CD" blockId="5.[787,1378,1919,2342]" pageId="5" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis id="EB8EEAF8FFC20D25FCC3F883FC18F840" bold="true" box="[788,943,1919,1948]" pageId="5" pageNumber="460">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="1EFA4D69FFC20D25FC6CF883FCEFF81F" authority="Thomas, 1897" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1897" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyproctidae" genus="Dasyprocta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="460" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kalinowskii">Dasyprocta kalinowskii Thomas, 1897</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="69923CB7FFC20D25FCBBF85AFB82F837" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3797735311" pageId="5" pageNumber="460">“Idma, Valley of Santa Ana, Cuzco, Peru. Alt. 4600 fect.”</materialsCitation>
This species is monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91E06561FFC20D25FCC4F7DCFCF0F754" pageId="5" pageNumber="460" type="distribution">
<caption id="8D856662FFC20D25FCC4F7DCFCF0F754" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6595261" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6595261" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6595261/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="460" targetBox="[173,763,1923,2337]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="D94536EAFFC20D25FCC4F7DCFCF0F754" blockId="5.[787,1378,1919,2342]" pageId="5" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis id="EB8EEAF8FFC20D25FCC4F7DCFC74F7E5" bold="true" box="[787,963,2080,2105]" pageId="5" pageNumber="460">Distribution.</emphasis>
S Peru, Urubamba and Marcapata drainages in the E slope of the Andes.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91E06561FFC20D25FCC4F773FAFBF647" pageId="5" pageNumber="460" type="description">
<paragraph id="D94536EAFFC20D25FCC4F773FAFBF647" blockId="5.[787,1378,1919,2342]" lastBlockId="5.[171,1379,2348,2931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis id="EB8EEAF8FFC20D25FCC4F773FBA2F76C" bold="true" box="[787,1045,2191,2224]" pageId="5" pageNumber="460">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 630 mm, tail 24 mm, hindfoot 125 mm (all measurements from the holotype). No specific data are available for body weight. Kalinowski’s 
<taxonomicName id="1EFA4D69FFC20D25FEE9F6D0FE2BF691" box="[318,412,2348,2381]" class="Mammalia" family="Cuniculidae" genus="Agouti" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="460" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Agouti</taxonomicName>
is large-sized. Upper parts of body are colored with hairs banded in black and yellowish rufous, with elongated hairs overhanging rump of white bases with black tips. Under parts are yellowish, grizzled with brown, and feet are blackish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91E06561FFC20D25FF7AF65AFD1FF635" pageId="5" pageNumber="460" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="D94536EAFFC20D25FF7AF65AFD1FF635" blockId="5.[171,1379,2348,2931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis id="EB8EEAF8FFC20D25FF7AF65AFEACF61F" bold="true" box="[173,283,2470,2499]" pageId="5" pageNumber="460">Habitat.</emphasis>
Montane tropical forest (Yungas ecoregion) in steep slopes of the eastern Andes at elevations of 1000-2000 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
